body:
- Both Synchronizing and populating “Synchronize view” of “Team Sync Perspective” often hangs – regardless if going through “Populate” or “Synchronize”;
- In `Progress` view, `Minimizing synchronization model` and `Updating Synchronize view for Git without local changes.` can be seen;
- I suspected this may have something to do with EMF files (Ecore or XMI) in one of the projects present in workspace, but I cannot verify with 100% certainty that this is somehow related – those files are present and committed, there are no changes in those files, yet same problem occurs;
- In all cases when this problem occurs, it causes Eclipse to stop responding and, when this happens, killing of Eclipse process is required in order to continue;
- Regardless of version of Eclipse and plugins used, frequency of occurrence of this problem completely disrupts normal work flow;
- Please see attached screenshots, screencasts, and log samples for details;

## Setup
**Eclipse IDE**: 
    • Version 2023-09 (4.29.0)
    • Build id: 4.29.0.20230907-1200
**JGit**: 6.7.0.202309050840-r
**EGit**: 6.7.0.202309050840-r
**OS**: Ubuntu 22.04.3 LTS
**Hardware**: Dell Precision 7560, Intel® Xeon(R) W-11855M CPU, 64 GB RAM, M.2 SSD disks

In case more details are needed, I also saved output from Eclipse IDE installation details “Configuration” tab: see attached `eclipse-20230907-1200_bndtools-7.0.0.REL_configuration.txt` file.

